 for bestpractices and # Buyer Dashboard

## Overview
Create a role-specific Buyer Dashboard for verified buyers that surfaces available auctions, watchlist, bidding history, subscription status, and saved filters. The page must enforce subscription gating and a KYC/verification workflow with admin approval. It should be built with a reuse-first approach leveraging the project's preferred stack (Next.js, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS on the frontend; Supabase with Postgres, RLS, Realtime on the backend; Stripe for payments; Vercel hosting). All code must be resilient to null/undefined values and guarded against common runtime pitfalls as described in the mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A role-specific, gated Buyer Dashboard for verified buyers that combines multiple subviews into a single, cohesive dashboard: 
  - Available Auctions (upcoming and current batches with real-time bid activity indicators)
  - Watchlist and Saved Searches (with alerts/notification settings)
  - Bidding History (recent bids, outcomes, and outbid notifications)
  - Subscription Status (current plan, renewal date, upgrade/renew options)
  - Saved Filters (category, location, condition, price range) with quick-load presets
  - KYC/Verification status indicator (with admin approval workflow status and call-to-action for pending items)

Goals:
- Gate access behind an active Stripe-based subscription and a verified KYC status with admin approval. If not authorized, present a guided onboarding/verification flow and appropriate upgrade prompts.
- Provide fast, responsive UX with clear data visualization shows (e.g., horizontal bar charts for activity, status pills for subscription, compact auction cards).
- Ensure data integrity and real-time responsiveness with Supabase Realtime for live bidding, and safe data handling on the client (null checks, array guards).

Connected features:
- Buyer Subscription & Verification: Access restricted by subscription plan and KYC/admin approval workflow. Admins review verification submissions and trigger status changes.
- Auction engine and live bidding data (read-only in this dashboard) feed from the real-time auction core.
- Saved filters and watchlists stored per-buyer in Supabase, with options to export or share saved searches (future feature).

UI elements and guidance:
- Auction Calendar / Upcoming Batches: list of scheduled auctions with date/time, location, asset summary, current bid, and a CTA to join or view details.
- Watchlist / Saved Searches: quick access cards, with alert toggles (email/SMS/push) and status indicators.
- Bid Activity: timeline-style or compact list with bid amount, time, status (won/lost/outbid), and action to view asset.
- Subscription Status Card: plan name, renewal date, remaining days, upgrade/cancel actions, and a lightweight credit/balance indicator if applicable.
- Filters/Quick Search: multi-select fields for category, location, condition, price range sliders, and saved presets.

Visual guidance:
- Adhere to the design system and color palette below. Ensure hierarchy is obvious (scores/stats, section titles, details), with strong contrast for CTAs and interactive elements.

## Components to Build
- BuyerDashboardPage
  - Layout wrapper with header, left content sections, and bottom navigation (persistent)
  - Subcomponents: AuctionCalendar, WatchlistPanel, BiddingHistoryPanel, SubscriptionStatusCard, SavedFiltersPanel, KYCBadge
- AuctionCard
  - Displays asset thumbnail, title, category, location, scheduled time, current bid, status tag
- AuctionList
  - Renders list of AuctionCard items with real-time bid updates
- WatchlistPanel
  - List of saved assets with alert toggles and quick actions
- SavedSearchCard
  - Saved filter presets with load/apply and edit/delete actions
- BiddingHistoryPanel
  - History rows with asset link, bid amount, timestamp, result
- SubscriptionStatusCard
  - Plan name, renewal date, status badge, upgrade CTA
- KYCVerificationPanel
  - Status badge, required actions, admin approval flow controls (for admin panel; viewer shows status and next steps)
- FiltersPanel
  - Category, location, condition, price range inputs with validation
- AlertsPanel (optional future enhancement)
  - Global notifications related to bids, verification, or subscription events
- DataVizBar
  - Minimalist horizontal bar chart visuals for quick stats (active/inactive segments)

Technical details:
- All components should gracefully handle data that may be null or undefined; use data ?? [] patterns and Array.isArray checks.
- Use useState<T[]>([]) for all array-based state; initialize with appropriate generic types.
- Ensure API data is validated and guarded:
  - const auctions = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - const items = data ?? []
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items: auctionsList = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages and routes
  - /buyer/dashboard (Role: buyer, requires subscription + verification)
- UI Components
  - Build responsive, accessible React components using TypeScript
  - Tailwind CSS utility classes for rapid styling
- State management
  - Local UI state with useState; global state for user session through Supabase Auth context
- Real-time data
  - Integrate Supabase Realtime for live bid updates
  - Safely connect to auction streams; implement reconnection logic
- Accessibility
  - Keyboard navigable, proper aria labels, sufficient color contrast
- Performance
  - Memoize expensive renders, use React.lazy/Suspense for heavy components if needed
- Data handling
  - Guard all array/map/filter/reduce calls with (items ?? []) or Array.isArray(item) checks
  - Validate API responses before rendering
- UI interactions
  - Hover/active states with neon yellow-green glow on actionable elements
  - Consistent card elevation, borders, and spacing per design system
- Security (frontend)
  - Hide gated sections for unauthorized users; show CTAs to upgrade/verify
  - Do not rely solely on frontend for gating; rely on backend authorization

### Backend
- APIs and endpoints (supabase functions / edge functions)
  - GET /buyer/dashboard: fetch combined data with:
    - auctions: Upcoming and current with live status
    - watchlist: user-specific
    - biddingHistory: recent bids
    - subscription: current plan and status
    - savedFilters: user saved filter presets
    - verificationStatus: KYC status + admin approval flag
  - PATCH/POST endpoints for:
    - Update watchlist item (toggle alerts)
    - Save/rename/delete filter presets
    - Update subscription status (on Stripe webhooks)
    - Submit KYC verification data (status flow)
  - Admin endpoints for verification approval workflow (admin panel integration)
- Database schema (examples)
  - buyers: id, user_id, subscription_id, kyc_status, verification_status, admin_approved, created_at, updated_at
  - subscriptions: id, buyer_id, plan_id, status, current_period_start, current_period_end, next_billing_date
  - auctions: id, asset_id, scheduled_at, batch_id, status, current_bid, reserve_price
  - watchlists: id, buyer_id, asset_id, alert_enabled, alert_preferences (JSON)
  - bids: id, buyer_id, auction_id, amount, created_at, status
  - saved_filters: id, buyer_id, name, filters (JSON), created_at
- Security
  - Use Row-Level Security (RLS) to restrict access to buyer-owned data
  - Validate inputs server-side; enforce rate limits on sensitive endpoints
- Payments
  - Stripe webhooks for subscription events; idempotent handling
  - Gate access on the server side based on subscription status and KYC verification

### Integration
- Data flow
  - BuyerDashboardPage fetches aggregated data from /buyer/dashboard
  - Real-time bid updates push to relevant auction cards via Supabase Realtime channel
  - Subscriptions and verifications gating logic runs on backend; frontend renders based on authenticated user state
- UI State Sync
  - When a user upgrades their plan or completes KYC, refresh dashboard data or optimistically reflect status changes
- Notifications
  - Email/SMS/Push for watchlist alerts and bid activity (configurable per user)

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on /buyer/dashboard
2. System checks authentication, then subscription status and KYC verification
   - If not authenticated: redirect to login
   - If not subscribed or KYC not verified: show gating panel guiding to upgrade and verification steps
3. Dashboard loads with:
   - Summary header: current subscription status, verification status
   - Upcoming Auctions panel: list with real-time bid data
   - Watchlist panel: saved assets and alert settings
   - Bidding History: recent activity with outcomes
   - Subscription Status Card: plan details and upgrade CTA
   - Saved Filters: quick-load saved searches
4. User interacts:
   - Join an auction or view details
   - Toggle watchlist alerts or save a new filter
   - Update or apply saved filters
   - Upgrade or initiate KYC verification if gated
5. Admin verification flow (admin actions, if accessed via admin route)
6. Real-time updates reflect bids, cancellations, or status changes instantly

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- buyers(user_id, kyc_status, verification_status, admin_approved, created_at, updated_at)
- subscriptions(id, buyer_id, plan_id, status, current_period_start, current_period_end, next_billing_date)
- auctions(id, asset_id, scheduled_at, status, current_bid, reserve_price, batch_id)
- bids(id, buyer_id, auction_id, amount, created_at, status)
- watchlists(id, buyer_id, asset_id, alert_enabled, alert_preferences)
- saved_filters(id, buyer_id, name, filters_json, created_at)
- assets(id, title, category, location, condition, price)
- kyc_records(id, buyer_id, status, admin_review_status, evidence, submitted_at)

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /api/buyer/dashboard
- GET /api/buyer/watchlist
- POST /api/buyer/watchlist/:asset_id/toggle
- GET /api/buyer/bidding-history
- GET /api/buyer/subscription
- GET /api/buyer/saved-filters
- POST /api/buyer/saved-filters
- PATCH /api/buyer/saved-filters/:id
- DELETE /api/buyer/saved-filters/:id
- POST /api/kyc/submit
- POST /api/kyc/verify/approve (admin)
- POST /api/kyc/verify/reject (admin)
- Stripe webhook: /webhooks/stripe (idempotent)

Security: [Authentication, authorization requirements]
- Authenticate with Supabase Auth; enforce user role 'buyer'
- Backend RP guards: check subscription.active, kyc.verified and admin_approved
- Use RLS policies for buyers data; restrict by user_id
- Ensure all endpoints validate inputs; use CSRF protection where applicable; strict rate limiting
- Webhooks must be idempotent and auditable; store event IDs

Validation: [Input validation rules]
- Filter inputs: category (string), location (string), condition (string), price_min/max (numbers within asset ranges)
- Saved filters: name unique per buyer per user
- KYC data: required fields validated on submit; admin approval status stored atomically
- Auctions: ensure scheduled_at in future or current; handle nulls gracefully

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Buyer Dashboard page renders only for authenticated, subscription-active, KYC-verified buyers; gated states show upgrade/verify prompts
- [ ] Auctions, watchlist, bidding history, and saved filters data are fetched safely with proper null guards: use data ?? [], Array.isArray checks
- [ ] Real-time bid updates appear in UI without race conditions; no null-crash when data is missing
- [ ] All array operations guarded (e.g., (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [])
- [ ] Subscriptions and KYC gating enforced server-side; Stripe webhooks are idempotent
- [ ] UI adheres to the design system: neon yellow-green accents, card shadows, grid spacing, accessible controls
